{"id": "EUVD-2025-20814", "enisaUuid": "c7d7ea11-17de-3b86-b2ff-1390a9d3dfc0", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nuserns and mnt_idmap leak in open_tree_attr(2)\n\nOnce want_mount_setattr() has returned a positive, it does require\nfinish_mount_kattr() to release ->mnt_userns.  Failing do_mount_setattr()\ndoes not change that.\n\nAs the result, we can end up leaking userns and possibly mnt_idmap as\nwell.", "datePublished": "2025-07-09T12:31:34", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-19T21:31:14", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/142db4e76110dd80239f4e79810f85ea1735ad60", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0748e553df0225754c316a92af3a77fdc057b358", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38247"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38247"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "447ce029-b4fd-3b76-9cfb-1e89e8ade44a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.15"}, {"id": "4cc0ce6d-3802-33ca-99fb-83ef86076be2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c4a16820d90199409c9bf01c4f794e1e9e8d8fd8 <0748e553df0225754c316a92af3a77fdc057b358"}, {"id": "8945e72c-3e23-38fa-9de7-c15b2c84a826", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.5"}, {"id": "9e6351d5-a079-322c-8495-b5c0ac3cf23c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c4a16820d90199409c9bf01c4f794e1e9e8d8fd8 <142db4e76110dd80239f4e79810f85ea1735ad60"}, {"id": "a8f4f51e-a910-37a7-9afd-511569c5483e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "aeeb732a-b1c9-3bb4-9caf-02f7b9212752", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc4"}, {"id": "e6cae4aa-28df-3c73-9121-29849011b57e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "3a6bdb0c-3044-3ca1-aad8-516d4f15be29", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}